 but exists entirely to entertain. Give the audience what they don’t know they want.” <strong>Ben Roberts</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>“The film that set me on the path to reading about cinema, thinking about it in ways I had never done before.” <strong>Jai arjun Singh</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>“One of Hitchcock’s most intriguing films, Psycho is a double portrait of a young woman on the run and a disturbed young man whose sexual impulses turn into murderous ones. The shower scene immediately comes to mind: the editing, the knife, the music, the lifeless eye of the heroine, the blood mixing with the water. It’s a truly terrifying sequence, even today.” <strong>Ava Cahen</strong></p>\r\n","quote":null,"credits":{"director":"Alfred Hitchcock","producer":"Alfred Hitchcock","writer":"Joseph Stefano","featuring":"Anthony Perkins, Vera Miles, John Gavin"},"year":"1960","nameAndYear":"Psycho (1960)","links":{"player":"","southbank":""},"player":null,"performances":[],"tags":["Shop"],"productionCountries":"USA","runningTime":108,"sightAndSound":{"results":[{"position":31,"tied":true,"category":"critics"},{"position":46,"tied":true,"category":"directors"}],"voters":null},"products":[{"sku":"5050582414738","name":"Psycho (DVD)","format":"DVD","url":"http://shop.bfi.org.uk/dvd-blu-ray/sight-and-sound-100-greatest-films-of-all-time/psycho-dvd.html","price":"5.99"},{"sku":"5050582776218","name":"Psycho (Blu-ray)","format":"Blu-Ray","url":"http://shop.bfi.org.uk/dvd-blu-ray/sight-and-sound-100-greatest-films-of-all-time/psycho-blu-ray.html","price":"8.99"}]},{"uuid":"98b20662-5754-5b8a-8e69-38fbec0d85c2","image":{"base":"https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/","relative":"2022-11/jaws-1975-swimmers-running-sea.jpg","main":"https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2022-11/jaws-1975-swimmers-running-sea.jpg/1920x1080-cropped/jaws-1975-swimmers-running-sea.jpg","thumb":"https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2022-11/