owing. Countless science-fiction blockbusters have tried to replicate it, but Scott’s original retains an unrepeatable intrigue in the central ambiguity of Deckard’s own identity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Science-fiction cinema is transformed forever in the furnace of production design.” <strong>Nigel Andrews</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Blade Runner distils the iconographies of dystopian science-fiction and transmogrifies them to produce the blueprint for seemingly every example of the genre to follow. As we have moved into the digital age and passed 2019, the year the film is set, Blade Runner’s analogue materiality now looks thoroughly retro-dystopian. But our deepest anxieties about the integrity of the self, our technology-constituted experience, environmental apocalypse and a polarised society in extremis have never felt more relevant.” <strong>Dario Llinares</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Lawrence G. Paull’s cityscapes, Jordan Cronenweth’s cinematography, Vangelis’s electronic score and Rutger Hauer’s soulful android were all astonishing innovations that redefined movie sci-fi.” <strong>Andy Lea</strong></p>\r\n","quote":null,"credits":{"director":"Ridley Scott","producer":"Michael Deeley","writer":"Hampton Fancher, David Webb Peoples","featuring":"Harrison Ford, Rutger Hauer, Sean Young"},"year":"1982","nameAndYear":"Blade Runner (1982)","links":{"player":"","southbank":""},"player":null,"performances":[],"tags":["Shop"],"productionCountries":"USA, Hong Kong","runningTime":117,"sightAndSound":{"results":[{"position":54,"tied":true,"category":"critics"},{"position":62,"tied":true,"category":"directors"}],"voters":null},"products":[{"sku":"7321902144825","name":"Blade Runner: The Final Cut (DVD)","format":"DVD","url":"http://shop.bfi.org.uk/dvd-blu-ray/sight-and-sound-100-greatest-films-of-all-time/blade-runner-the-final-cut-dvd.html","price":"9.99"}]},{"uuid":"b58b75d7-e9e2-5a1f-a448-afa92a35462d","image":{"base":"https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/","relative":"2022-