y every example of the genre to follow. As we have moved into the digital age and passed 2019, the year the film is set, Blade Runner’s analogue materiality now looks thoroughly retro-dystopian. But our deepest anxieties about the integrity of the self, our technology-constituted experience, environmental apocalypse and a polarised society in extremis have never felt more relevant.” <strong>Dario Llinares</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Lawrence G. Paull’s cityscapes, Jordan Cronenweth’s cinematography, Vangelis’s electronic score and Rutger Hauer’s soulful android were all astonishing innovations that redefined movie sci-fi.” <strong>Andy Lea</strong></p>\r\n","quote":null,"credits":{"director":"Ridley Scott","producer":"Michael Deeley","writer":"Hampton Fancher, David Webb Peoples","featuring":"Harrison Ford, Rutger Hauer, Sean Young"},"year":"1982","nameAndYear":"Blade Runner (1982)","links":{"player":"","southbank":""},"player":null,"performances":[],"tags":["Shop"],"productionCountries":"USA, Hong Kong","runningTime":117,"sightAndSound":{"results":[{"position":54,"tied":true,"category":"critics"},{"position":62,"tied":true,"category":"directors"}],"voters":null},"products":[{"sku":"7321902144825","name":"Blade Runner: The Final Cut (DVD)","format":"DVD","url":"http://shop.bfi.org.uk/dvd-blu-ray/sight-and-sound-100-greatest-films-of-all-time/blade-runner-the-final-cut-dvd.html","price":"9.99"}]},"comments":[{"type":"p","key":"A sci-fi film like no other. I've never quite understood the theory that Deckard (Harrison Ford) is a replicant, because to me this is a story about a man taught to value life by those who need more of it. Refined over the years by re-edits, it's the perfect example of the wonder of the genre. ","ref":null,"props":{"children":"A sci-fi film like no other. I've never quite understood the theory that Deckard (Harrison Ford) is a replicant, because to me this is a story about a man taught to value life by those who need more of it. Refined over the ye